Program: Free Thinking
Title: Wombs on Legs? Science Fiction and the Control of Reproduction
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03g2wkp
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 28 Aug 2014
From HG Wells and Margaret Atwood to Battlestar Galactica, science fiction texts and tv series have long used birth control as a metaphor for the limits on individual freedom. Sarah Dillon, from the University of St Andrews, looks at the roles for women which science fiction has imagined and asks is sci-fi sexist? Producer: Luke Mulhall First broadcast in November 2013. Show less